trans-unit.source: Import/Export Service Log File Format
trans-unit.target: Import/Export Service Log File Format

trans-unit.source: When the Microsoft Azure Import/Export service performs an action on a drive as part of an import job or an export job, logs are written to block blobs in the storage account associated with that job.
trans-unit.target: When the Microsoft Azure Import/Export service performs an action on a drive as part of an import job or an export job, logs are written to block blobs in the storage account associated with that job.

trans-unit.source: There are two logs that may be written by the Import/Export service:
trans-unit.target: There are two logs that may be written by the Import/Export service:

trans-unit.source: The error log is always generated in the event of an error.
trans-unit.target: The error log is always generated in the event of an error.

trans-unit.source: The verbose log is not enabled by default, but may be enabled by setting the <languageKeyword>EnableVerboseLog</languageKeyword> property on a <link xlink:href="2f703ff1-d52b-43bd-81ec-90350a39e2af" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Put Job</link> or <link xlink:href="6f83d480-c09e-4e3b-b096-46e140e8c93d" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Update Job Properties</link> operation.
trans-unit.target: The verbose log is not enabled by default, but may be enabled by setting the <languageKeyword>EnableVerboseLog</languageKeyword> property on a <link xlink:href="2f703ff1-d52b-43bd-81ec-90350a39e2af" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Put Job</link> or <link xlink:href="6f83d480-c09e-4e3b-b096-46e140e8c93d" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Update Job Properties</link> operation.

trans-unit.source: Log File Location
trans-unit.target: Log File Location

trans-unit.source: The logs are written to block blobs in the container or virtual directory specified by the <languageKeyword>ImportExportStatesPath</languageKeyword> setting, which you can set on a <languageKeyword>Put Job</languageKeyword> operation.
trans-unit.target: The logs are written to block blobs in the container or virtual directory specified by the <languageKeyword>ImportExportStatesPath</languageKeyword> setting, which you can set on a <languageKeyword>Put Job</languageKeyword> operation.

trans-unit.source: The location to which the logs are written depends on how authentication is specified for the job, together with the value specified for <languageKeyword>ImportExportStatesPath</languageKeyword>.
trans-unit.target: The location to which the logs are written depends on how authentication is specified for the job, together with the value specified for <languageKeyword>ImportExportStatesPath</languageKeyword>.

trans-unit.source: Authentication for the job may be specified via a storage account key, or a container SAS (shared access signature).
trans-unit.target: Authentication for the job may be specified via a storage account key, or a container SAS (shared access signature).

trans-unit.source: The name of the container or virtual directory may either be the default name of <parameterReference>waimportexport</parameterReference>, or another container or virtual directory name that you specify.
trans-unit.target: The name of the container or virtual directory may either be the default name of <parameterReference>waimportexport</parameterReference>, or another container or virtual directory name that you specify.

trans-unit.source: The logs are available after processing of the drive is complete.
trans-unit.target: The logs are available after processing of the drive is complete.

trans-unit.source: Log File Format
trans-unit.target: Log File Format

trans-unit.source: The format for both logs is the same: a blob containing XML descriptions of the events that occurred while copying blobs between the hard drive and the customer's account.
trans-unit.target: The format for both logs is the same: a blob containing XML descriptions of the events that occurred while copying blobs between the hard drive and the customer's account.

trans-unit.source: The verbose log contains complete information about the status of the copy operation for every blob (for an import job) or file (for an export job), whereas the error log contains only the information for blobs or files that encountered errors during the import or export job.
trans-unit.target: The verbose log contains complete information about the status of the copy operation for every blob (for an import job) or file (for an export job), whereas the error log contains only the information for blobs or files that encountered errors during the import or export job.

trans-unit.source: The verbose log format is shown below.
trans-unit.target: The verbose log format is shown below.

trans-unit.source: The error log has the same structure, but filters out successful operations.
trans-unit.target: The error log has the same structure, but filters out successful operations.
